ll be accepted on a rolling basis during the fall and spring semesters  Proposals should be submitted at least two weeks prior to the travel date so that adequate time is available to review the proposal and make a funding award  If the request is for international travel  permission from the Office of International Programs is required before submitting a funding request to V CUR  To request funds for Cadet Research Related Travel  complete the Undergraduate Research Cadet Travel Application and email it to Leslie Joyce  joycelh vmi edu  in the V CUR office  Your faculty advisor must also submit a letter or email of support coincident with this application  This letter must address the availability of other possible funding sources  e g  your department  If you will be presenting at MARCUS NCUR or the Big South  please send notice to Leslie Joyce by email  Funding for travel to these conferences will be managed as a group  Individual requests are not required  Funding for Research Grants  Contracts Etc  External Funding Internal Funding    Wetmore Funds Foreign Travel Jackson Hope Research Related Travel VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 